  "text": "Similar to us, [CITATION_1] assume that success and failure of treatment are unobservable and unverifiable, but they do not consider the problem of subjective evaluation. In contrast to our model, in which treatments are vertically differentiated, in their setting differentiation is horizontal so that the problem of overtreatment cannot appear.",
